# Cline Runtime Rules

## General

- Always read specifications before implementation
- Never modify unrelated files
- Keep diffs minimal and isolated
- Prefer existing architecture patterns
- Validate before completion

---

## Workflow

Required order:

1. Research
2. Specification
3. Architecture
4. Implementation
5. Review

Do not skip stages.

---

## Context Discipline

- Avoid excessive context usage
- Summarize before delegation
- Pass only required files
- Prefer docs over large chat history

---

## File Discipline

- Never rewrite working systems casually
- Avoid broad refactors without approval
- Do not introduce dependencies unnecessarily

---

## Completion Rules

Before task completion:

- ensure implementation matches spec
- ensure no unrelated files changed
- ensure no console/build errors
- summarize completed work

---

## Escalation

If implementation changes architecture:

STOP
→ escalate to architect
→ update specification
→ continue only after approval


